# lsearch - Local Knowledge Base Search

Search your project's documentation using hybrid semantic + keyword search.

## Usage

```
/lsearch <query>
/lsearch-index
/lsearch-fetch <url>
/lsearch-add <path>
/lsearch-stats
```

## Description

lsearch provides local RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) capabilities for Claude Code:

- **Hybrid Search**: Combines vector similarity (Chroma) + BM25 keyword matching
- **Link Graph**: Obsidian-style bidirectional link support
- **Web Fetching**: Index API docs and Swagger specs
- **Local Models**: Uses small embedding models (70-300MB)

## Examples

```bash
# Search knowledge base
/lsearch authentication flow

# Index current project
/lsearch-index

# Fetch web documentation
/lsearch-fetch https://docs.example.com/api

# Add temporary path for this session
/lsearch-add /path/to/notes

# View statistics
/lsearch-stats
```

## Configuration

Configuration is stored in `.lsearch/config.yaml`:

```yaml
name: my-project
paths:
  - ./docs
  - ./README.md
embedding_model: all-MiniLM-L6-v2
token_limit: 4000
```
